- blogs.push({ id: 1, title: 'Getting started with insurance templates', slug: 'getting-started-insurance-templates', date: '2025-02-15', author: 'Sarah Chen', category: 'Templates', image: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1450101499163-c8848c66ca85?w=800&auto=format&fit=crop', excerpt: 'Learn how to use Trufla templates for payments and claims from day one.', content: '<p>Insurance templates can streamline your workflow and keep documents consistent. This guide walks you through setting up your first template, customizing fields, and sharing with your team.</p><p>We recommend starting with the claims assistance template, then adding payment templates as your team grows. All templates are designed to be editable and compliant with common regulations.</p><h3>Key steps</h3><p>Download the template pack, open in your preferred editor, and replace placeholder text with your company details. Use the style guide included to keep branding consistent.</p>', comments: [{ author: 'Alex R.', date: '2025-02-16', text: 'Exactly what I needed. Set up in under an hour.' }, { author: 'Jordan K.', date: '2025-02-17', text: 'Clear and practical. Thank you.' }] })
- blogs.push({ id: 2, title: 'Best practices for claims documentation', slug: 'best-practices-claims-documentation', date: '2025-02-12', author: 'James Mitchell', category: 'Claims', image: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1589829545856-d10d557cf95f?w=800&auto=format&fit=crop', excerpt: 'Keep claims clear, complete, and audit-ready with these practices.', content: '<p>Good documentation reduces disputes and speeds up resolution. In this post we cover how to structure claim forms, what to include in supporting documents, and how to archive for future reference.</p><p>Always include dates, reference numbers, and a short summary at the top. Attach evidence in a logical order and name files consistently.</p>', comments: [] })
- blogs.push({ id: 3, title: 'Scaling payment workflows', slug: 'scaling-payment-workflows', date: '2025-02-10', author: 'Priya Sharma', category: 'Payments', image: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1554224155-6726b3ff858f?w=800&auto=format&fit=crop', excerpt: 'Scale your payment processes without adding headcount.', content: '<p>As volume grows, manual payment handling becomes a bottleneck. We look at template-based workflows, approval chains, and reporting so you can scale without losing control.</p><p>Start by mapping your current process, then identify steps that can be standardized with templates. Roll out one workflow at a time and gather feedback.</p>', comments: [{ author: 'Sam T.', date: '2025-02-11', text: 'We applied this and saw a real improvement in throughput.' }] })
- blogs.push({ id: 4, title: 'Template updates and compliance', slug: 'template-updates-compliance', date: '2025-02-08', author: 'Sarah Chen', category: 'Templates', image: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507925921958-8a62f3d1a50d?w=800&auto=format&fit=crop', excerpt: 'How we keep templates up to date with regulation changes.', content: '<p>Regulations change; your templates should too. We review our template set quarterly and publish release notes. This post explains how we track changes and how you can subscribe to updates.</p><p>Major changes are versioned. You can stay on an older version during a transition period if needed.</p>', comments: [] })
- blogs.push({ id: 5, title: 'Customer success: reducing claim cycle time', slug: 'customer-success-claim-cycle-time', date: '2025-02-05', author: 'James Mitchell', category: 'Claims', image: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1557804506-669a67965ba0?w=800&auto=format&fit=crop', excerpt: 'A case study on cutting claim cycle time with better templates.', content: '<p>One of our clients cut average claim cycle time by 30% after switching to structured templates. We share what they changed and how you can apply the same approach.</p><p>Key factors were consistent fields across all claim types, clear instructions for adjusters, and a simple checklist for completeness.</p>', comments: [] })
- blogs.push({ id: 6, title: 'Integrating templates with your tools', slug: 'integrating-templates-tools', date: '2025-02-01', author: 'Priya Sharma', category: 'Templates', image: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1460925895917-afdab827c52f?w=800&auto=format&fit=crop', excerpt: 'Use Trufla templates inside your existing systems.', content: '<p>Our templates are available in multiple formats so you can use them in your CRM, document management system, or email. This post covers export options and simple integration patterns.</p><p>We support PDF, Word, and structured data export. API access is available for enterprise plans.</p>', comments: [] })
- blogs.push({ id: 7, title: 'Payment security and templates', slug: 'payment-security-templates', date: '2025-01-28', author: 'Sarah Chen', category: 'Payments', image: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1563013544-824ae1b704d3?w=800&auto=format&fit=crop', excerpt: 'Keeping payment instructions secure when using shared templates.', content: '<p>Templates should never contain live account numbers or sensitive data. We outline how to separate structure from secrets and how to handle payment details safely.</p><p>Use placeholders in templates and fill in details through a secure channel. Restrict edit access to payment fields.</p>', comments: [] })
- blogs.push({ id: 8, title: 'Quick wins for claims teams', slug: 'quick-wins-claims-teams', date: '2025-01-25', author: 'James Mitchell', category: 'Claims', image: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1552664730-d307ca884978?w=800&auto=format&fit=crop', excerpt: "Three changes that improved one team's claims process in a week.", content: '<p>Small changes can have a big impact. We share three quick wins: a standard cover sheet, a one-page checklist, and a single folder structure for attachments.</p><p>All three use our free templates. You can implement them without IT support.</p>', comments: [] })
